main event: A large, aluminum-colored, cross-like object was observed hovering to the north, then turning east, reaching a position of 16o-20' and turning toward the moon before disappearing after 18 seconds.
interesting points: The object was described as saucer-like in appearance and maneuvered at high speed from north to south.
The sighting lasted from 12:00 AM to 3:00 AM, with the object being observed at 8-10 miles southeast of Wheaton, Maryland.
Weather and wind conditions indicated the object was not a conventional aircraft.
Other similar sightings had been reported in the area.
The report was considered of interest by the headquarters, but no further investigation was deemed necessary as the sighting was believed to have been satisfactorily explained.
